CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. 11, reads: "Greet Exchange Pastor - The Rev. Charles L. Lewis, center, pastor of the United Church of Canada, Windsor, Ont., was cordially welcomed Sunday as he assumed pastoral responsibilities at Warren Methodist Church for the month of August, on the interracial pastoral exchange project, which finds the Rev. Ramsey Bridges, Warren's pastor, at the helm of the United Church of Canada for the month. Warren officers, surrounding the Rev. and Mrs. Lewis and their son, Peter, are, left to right: William Easley, Atty. Thomas Barton (to their left); Wayland Bryant, Mrs. Beatrice Makel, John White and Harry Coleman. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: William Easley, Wayland Bryant, Mrs. Lewis, Peter Lewis, Rev. Lewis, Atty. Thomas Barton, Beatrice Makel, John White, and Harry Coleman, standing in Warren Methodist Church
